<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                                    Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-08">September 8,
                                        1944</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Secretary of
                                    War</hi></p>
                            <p>As a result of years of Fascist and Nazi rule and the destruction
                                resulting from the battles on its soil, I understand that the supply
                                situation in Italy is critical.</p>
                            <p>This situation should be corrected as effectively and as quickly as
                                possible.</p>
                            <p>The War Department should, therefore, take immediate action to make
                                available the additional essential civilian supplies and shipping
                                necessary to remedy this condition.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>